# Advanced Snapping Patterns

Beyond basic snapping, there are sophisticated patterns and strategies.

## Multi-level Snapping

Snap in stages with increasing precision:

```javascript
function multiLevelSnap(point, levels) {
  let current = point;

  for (const level of levels) {
    const snapper = new PythagoreanSnapper(level.threshold);
    const result = snapper.snap(current);

    if (result.didSnap) {
      current = result.snapped;
    }
  }

  return current;
}

// Usage: coarse to fine
multiLevelSnap(point, [
  { threshold: 0.5 },  // Coarse snap
  { threshold: 0.1 },  // Medium snap
  { threshold: 0.01 }  // Fine snap
]);
```

## Directional Snapping

Snap along specific directions:

```javascript
function directionalSnap(point, direction, threshold) {
  // Snap only along the specified direction
  const projected = projectOntoDirection(point, direction);
  return snapToPythagorean(projected, threshold);
}
```

## Constraint Chaining

Combine multiple constraint types:

```javascript
function constrainedSnap(point, constraints) {
  let result = point;

  for (const constraint of constraints) {
    result = constraint.apply(result);

    if (!constraint.satisfied(result)) {
      return null; // Constraint violation
    }
  }

  return result;
}
```

## Adaptive Precision

Adjust snapping based on context:

```javascript
function adaptiveSnap(point, context) {
  const threshold = calculateThreshold(context);
  const snapResult = snap(point, threshold);

  // Refine based on snap quality
  if (snapResult.distance > threshold * 0.8) {
    // Near boundary, use more precise check
    return preciseSnap(point, threshold * 0.5);
  }

  return snapResult;
}

