# Common Pitfalls and Solutions

Avoid these common mistakes when implementing snapping systems.

## Pitfall 1: Threshold Too Small
**Problem**: Few or no points snap

```javascript
// BAD
const threshold = 0.0001; // Too strict!

// GOOD
const threshold = 0.1; // Reasonable for most cases
```

## Pitfall 2: Threshold Too Large
**Problem**: Points snap incorrectly

```javascript
// BAD
const threshold = 10.0; // Way too large!

// GOOD
const threshold = Math.max(0.1, coordinateMagnitude * 0.01);
```

## Pitfall 3: Floating-Point Precision Issues
**Problem**: Precision errors cause incorrect behavior

```javascript
// BAD
if (distance == threshold) // Never compare floats directly!

// GOOD
if (Math.abs(distance - threshold) < EPSILON)
```

## Pitfall 4: Not Checking All Triples
**Problem**: Miss closer snap points

```javascript
// BAD - returns first match
for (const triple of triples) {
  if (distance < threshold) {
    return triple; // Returns first, not closest!
  }
}

// GOOD - tracks closest
let closest = null;
let minDistance = Infinity;

for (const triple of triples) {
  if (distance < threshold && distance < minDistance) {
    closest = triple;
    minDistance = distance;
  }
}

return closest;
```

## Pitfall 5: Ignoring Edge Cases
**Problem**: Crashes on unusual inputs

```javascript
// BAD - assumes valid input
function snap(point) {
  return snapToPythagorean(point.x, point.y);
}

// GOOD - validates input
function snap(point) {
  if (!point || typeof point.x !== 'number' || typeof point.y !== 'number') {
    throw new Error('Invalid point');
  }

  if (!isFinite(point.x) || !isFinite(point.y)) {
    throw new Error('Point must be finite');
  }

  return snapToPythagorean(point.x, point.y);
}
```

## Pitfall 6: Not Caching Results
**Problem**: Repeated expensive calculations

```javascript
// GOOD - cache snap results
class CachedSnapper {
  constructor(threshold) {
    this.threshold = threshold;
    this.cache = new Map();
  }

  snap(point) {
    const key = `${point.x},${point.y}`;

    if (this.cache.has(key)) {
      return this.cache.get(key);
    }

    const result = this.performSnap(point);
    this.cache.set(key, result);

    return result;
  }
}

