# Real-World Applications

Pythagorean snapping has numerous practical applications.

## 1. Computer-Aided Design (CAD)

**Use Case**: Ensure dimensions satisfy design constraints

```javascript
// CAD dimension snapping
function snapDimension(dimension, standardSizes) {
  for (const size of standardSizes) {
    if (Math.abs(dimension - size) < tolerance) {
      return size;
    }
  }
  return dimension;
}

// Example: Architectural standards
const standardLengths = [3, 6, 9, 12, 15]; // feet
const snapLength = snapDimension(11.95, standardLengths);
// Returns: 12 (snapped to standard 12' length)
```

## 2. Computer Graphics

**Use Case**: Vertex placement on regular grids

```javascript
// Grid snapping for 3D modeling
function snapVertex(vertex, gridSize) {
  return {
    x: Math.round(vertex.x / gridSize) * gridSize,
    y: Math.round(vertex.y / gridSize) * gridSize,
    z: Math.round(vertex.z / gridSize) * gridSize
  };
}
```

## 3. Game Development

**Use Case**: Object placement and collision detection

```javascript
// Snap game objects to valid positions
function snapObjectPosition(position, validPositions) {
  let closest = null;
  let minDist = Infinity;

  for (const valid of validPositions) {
    const dist = distance(position, valid);

    if (dist < SNAP_THRESHOLD && dist < minDist) {
      closest = valid;
      minDist = dist;
    }
  }

  return closest || position;
}
```

## 4. Data Visualization

**Use Case**: Align data points to meaningful values

```javascript
// Snap chart values to nice numbers
function snapToNiceNumber(value) {
  const niceNumbers = [0.1, 0.2, 0.5, 1, 2, 5, 10, 20, 50, 100];
  const magnitude = Math.pow(10, Math.floor(Math.log10(value)));

  for (const nice of niceNumbers) {
    const candidate = nice * magnitude;
    if (Math.abs(value - candidate) < magnitude * 0.2) {
      return candidate;
    }
  }

  return value;
}
```

## 5. Robotics

**Use Case**: Path planning with discrete waypoints

```javascript
// Snap robot path to valid waypoints
function snapWaypoint(point, validWaypoints) {
  return findNearestValidPoint(point, validWaypoints, SNAP_RADIUS);
}
```

## Case Study: Architectural Design

**Problem**: Ensure building dimensions follow modular design principles

**Solution**: Snap all dimensions to standard modules

```javascript
// Modular dimension system
const MODULE = 4; // 4-foot modules

function snapDimensionToModule(dimension) {
  const modules = Math.round(dimension / MODULE);
  return modules * MODULE;
}

// Example
snapDimensionToModule(11.8); // Returns: 12 (3 modules)
